kb:nemo-speech rdf:type     ktype:Feature ;
               rdfs:label   "NVIDIA NeMo Speech" ;
               kpred:has-status   "planned" ;
               kpred:description  "GPU-accelerated STT and TTS via NVIDIA NeMo (Apache 2.0). Python sidecar or Docker container. Models: Nemotron-3.5-ASR-Streaming-0.6B (40 languages, 80ms-1s latency), MagpieTTS v2602 (9 languages). Requires NVIDIA GPU + CUDA. Fallback to existing Whisper+Kokoro WASM for non-NVIDIA users." ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:whisper-stt ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:kokoro-tts ;
               kpred:open-question "Sidecar architecture: Docker Compose, standalone FastAPI, or Ollama-style model runner? Need /transcribe and /synthesize HTTP endpoints matching existing provider pattern." ;
               kpred:open-question "Dev setup: separate repo or monorepo subfolder like mcp-server/? Python 3.12+ with uv for dependency management." .

kb:cosmos-nano rdf:type     ktype:Feature ;
               rdfs:label   "NVIDIA Cosmos3-Nano" ;
               kpred:has-status   "speculative" ;
               kpred:description  "16B-parameter omnimodal world foundation model for Physical AI. Generates and reasons over video, images, audio, and robot actions. OpenMDW 1.1 licence (commercial use). Requires NVIDIA GPU (Ampere/Hopper/Blackwell), BF16 precision, Linux. Potential uses: generate preview animations from entity descriptions, 3D scene understanding for graph visualisation, multimodal KB ingest (video/image/audio sources). Shares NVIDIA GPU sidecar infrastructure with NeMo Speech." ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:nemo-speech ;
               kpred:open-question "Massive resource requirements (16B params, BF16) — viable only for users with high-end NVIDIA GPUs. Evaluate smaller distilled variants when available." ;
               kpred:open-question "Integration path: same Python sidecar as NeMo Speech? Separate container? Which Cosmos capabilities map to KB workflows (video→triples, entity→animation)?" .

