               kpred:feature-id   "F39" ;
               kpred:has-status   "planned" ;
               kpred:description  "Order the roadmap and other reference graphs properly using the existing nav vocabulary (hnav: = urn:reckons:nav/, consumed by src/lib/rdf/hierarchy.ts): hnav:order (position, meta/hidden), skos:broader (tree parent), hnav:layer (depth), hnav:next/hnav:prev (visible sequence edges). Adds a NEW hnav:sequential \"true\"^^xsd:boolean flag on a parent/story node meaning its ordered children are a LOCKED front-to-back reading (no random access) — 'a story can sometimes only be read front to back'. First worked target: the enterprise phase chain (kb:ent-phase-1..4) and currents phases as ordered, sequential sub-trees; then a full pass tagging feature epics/themes as tree parents. hierarchy.ts + the story player need to learn hnav:sequential to enforce the locked traversal." ;
